<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-20T08:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-20T08:40:00-05:00" n="234" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1884</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-20T09:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1916, 9 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Fourth Regiment Marines arrived yesterday and after colonel had
                            interviews with Caperton and myself left here last night for Monte
                            Cristi preparatory to occupying Santiago, Moca and La Vega if necessary.
                            Deadlock continues in the House, no immediate election President seems
                            probable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>